     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Socioeconomic impact assessment of COVID-19 in Thailand
2. Socioeconomic impact assessment of COVID-19 in Phuket</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. The UN in Thailand, under the leadership of UNDP and UNICEF and in partnership with other development agencies, has responded to support the country by undertaking a socio-economic impact assessment in close collaboration with the National Economic and Social Development Council (NESDC). The finding of the assessment was presented in the joint UN-NESDC seminar in September 2020. It suggested that ensuring a sustainable recovery for Thailand requires safeguarding resources for the most vulnerable. At the same time, the country needs to restructure its development path towards more domestic economy-oriented and greener growth model, leveraging its natural capital, reduce its vulnerability to external shocks, and position its economy in the post-COVID value chains.

2. UNDP has also conducted a subnational socioeconomic impact assessment for Phuket as per the request of the Tourism Authority of Thailand, the Thai Chamber of Commerce, and the Phuket Chamber of Commerce. The assessment entails analyzing the COVID-19 impacts&#x2014;particularly on its most vulnerable populations. It stressed the need to diversify Phuket&#x2019;s economy and reduce its dependence on tourism, or the province will risk falling into poverty. Building on this assessment, subsequent studies on Phuket recovery vision and strategy was developed, which helped inform Phuket&#x2019;s latest Provincial Development Plan.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
